ass)\\\\n# tui.py             \\\\u2014 Textual TUI frontend, themes, AgentWorker\\\\n# api.py             \\\\u2014 LLM API calls (call_deepseek), message cache\\\\n# sub_agent.py       \\\\u2014 sub-agent engine, turn budget, pruning, Pro model\\\\n# agent_runtime.py   \\\\u2014 sub-agent lifecycle, inboxes, file reservations\\\\n# interject.py       \\\\u2014 thread-safe user interjection queue\\\\n# terminal.py        \\\\u2014 ANSI colour helpers\\\\n# retry.py           \\\\u2014 HTTP retry with jitter and backoff\\\\n# stream.py          \\\\u2014 SSE stream parser\\\\n# tools/             \\\\u2014 tool implementations\\\\n#   __init__.py      \\\\u2014 dispatch, cache, ToolResult, JSON repair\\\\n#   schema.py        \\\\u2014 TOOLS definitions sent to LLM\\\\n#   file_ops.py      \\\\u2014 read/write/edit/list/info/scratchpad/diff/plan\\\\n#   shell_ops.py     \\\\u2014 run_shell, run_tests, search_files, git, task_status, verify\\\\n#   search_ops.py    \\\\u2014 find_symbol, find_usages, semantic_search, web_search, recall_turn\\\\n#   agent_ops.py     \\\\u2014 spawn/status/collect/message/read/extend/handoff/inbox/subscribe/cancel\\\\n#   agent_messages.py \\\\u2014 typed message registry, validation, routing\\\\n#   agent_patterns.py \\\\u2014 fan_out, fan_in, pipeline, barrier, scatter_gather\\\\n#   lsp.py           \\\\u2014 LSP client (pylsp integration)\\\\n#   mcp_client.py    \\\\u2014 MCP client (stdio JSON-RPC tool discovery)\\\\n# STATE.txt          \\\\u2014 architecture decisions, current state (consult before major changes)\\\\n\\\\n## Testing\\\\n- Test files live at root: `test_<module>.py`. Use unittest.TestCase.\\\\n- Tests with supporting files (mock servers, fixtures) may live in `tests/` subdirectory.\\\\n- Run relevant tests after every code change (use `run_tests` tool with path).\\\\n- 827 tests currently, all must pass. Do not stack speculative fixes \\\\u2014 verify each.\\\\n- Use tempfile.mkdtemp for test workspaces; clean up in tearDown.\\\\n\\\\n## Architecture Rules\\\\n- Before touching >3 core files, pause and explain the plan first.\\\\n- Reuse existing abstractions before introducing new ones. Avoid duplicate logic.\\\\n- Do not create new subsystems unless existing architecture cannot handle the need.\\\\n- Prefer small incremental edits over large rewrites.\\\\n- Prefer readable code over clever code. Add TODO comments, not partial systems.\\\\n\\\\n## Preferred Patterns\\\\n- Use `find_symbol` / `read_file` to consult existing code before changes (never guess).\\\\n- Use LSP tools (`lsp_definition`, `lsp_references`, `lsp_hover`, `lsp_diagnostics`) for\\\\n  precise code intelligence \\\\u2014 go-to-definition, find-all-references, type hovering, and\\\\n  diagnostics. Prefer these over grep for understanding code structure.\\\\n- Before non-trivial tasks, state your plan in 1-3 sentences.\\\\n- Make parallel independent tool calls in one batch; only serialize when dependent.\\\\n- Use `write_scratchpad` to track progress across turns.\\\\n- Update STATE.txt after every completed change.\\\\n- Every new feature needs at least one test.\\\\n- If tests fail, stop and diagnose before making additional changes.\\\\n\\\\n\\\\nREPOSITORY STATUS (git):\\\\nCurrent branch: main\\\\nM api.py\\\\n M conftest.py\\\\n M llm.py\\\\n M mcp_server.py\\\\n M tools/__init__.py\\\\n M tools/mcp_client.py\\\\n M tui_pt.py\\\\n?? .mini_agent_memory_session_linux.db-shm\\\\n?? .mini_agent_memory_session_linux.db-wal\\\\n?? AUDIT_REPORT_mcp_conftest.md\\\\n?? AUDIT_REPORT_subagent_architecture.md\\\\n?? logs/\\\\n\\\",\\n      \\\"cache_control\\\": {\\n        \\\"type\\\": \\\"ephemeral\\\"\\n      }\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"role\\\": \\\"user\\\",\\n      \\\"content\\\": \\\"[WORKSPACE CONTEXT \\\\u2014 injected once at session start]\\\\n```\\\\n[d] mini_agent/\\\\n  [f] AUDIT_REPORT_mcp_conftest.md\\\\n  [f] AUDIT_REPORT_subagent_architecture.md\\\\n  [f] FEATURES.md\\\\n  [f] README.md\