ssing 2 required positional arguments: '_write_gate' and '_read_gate'\\\\n```\\\\n\\\\nThese two are likely connected: the SSE error causes tool execution to fail during streaming, which leaves orphaned tool_calls in the message history, which causes the 400 on the next API call.\\\\n\\\\nNow, WHY does `_mcp_discover` get called without gates? Let me look at the actual dispatch and the _on_tool_ready callback one more time. But also let me check if there's a DIFFERENT `_on_tool_ready` that might be used in sub-agent context.\\\\n\\\\nActually, you know what - let me look at sub_agent.py since that's where MCP tools are most likely called repeatedly.\\\",\\n      \\\"tool_calls\\\": [\\n        {\\n          \\\"id\\\": \\\"call_00_S4XgZYgOZbxd7m4LIZ9p7536\\\",\\n          \\\"type\\\": \\\"function\\\",\\n          \\\"function\\\": {\\n            \\\"name\\\": \\\"search_files\\\",\\n            \\\"arguments\\\": \\\"{\\\\\\\"pattern\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"on_tool_ready|_api_call_phase|execute_tool\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"path\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"/Users/gabrielmalone/Desktop/mini_agent/sub_agent.py\\\\\\\"}\\\"\\n          }\\n        }\\n      ]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"role\\\": \\\"tool\\\",\\n      \\\"tool_call_id\\\": \\\"call_00_S4XgZYgOZbxd7m4LIZ9p7536\\\",\\n      \\\"content\\\": \\\"{\\\\\\\"success\\\\\\\": true, \\\\\\\"content\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"No matches for 'on_tool_ready|_api_call_phase|execute_tool' in /Users/gabrielmalone/Desktop/mini_agent/sub_agent.py\\\\\\\"}\\\"\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"role\\\": \\\"assistant\\\",\\n      \\\"content\\\": \\\"\\\",\\n      \\\"reasoning_content\\\": \\\"OK so sub_agent.py doesn't have its own on_tool_ready or _api_call_phase - it must use the ones from llm.py. Let me check what sub_agent.py imports and how it runs turns.\\\",\\n      \\\"tool_calls\\\": [\\n        {\\n          \\\"id\\\": \\\"call_00_3ajgxS4v3jguZdjdKiP31017\\\",\\n          \\\"type\\\": \\\"function\\\",\\n          \\\"function\\\": {\\n      