ive at root: `test_<module>.py`. Use unittest.TestCase.\n- Tests with supporting files (mock servers, fixtures) may live in `tests/` subdirectory.\n- Run relevant tests after every code change (use `run_tests` tool with path).\n- 827 tests currently, all must pass. Do not stack speculative fixes \u2014 verify each.\n- Use tempfile.mkdtemp for test workspaces; clean up in tearDown.\n\n## Architecture Rules\n- Before touching >3 core files, pause and explain the plan first.\n- Reuse existing abstractions before introducing new ones. Avoid duplicate logic.\n- Do not create new subsystems unless existing architecture cannot handle the need.\n- Prefer small incremental edits over large rewrites.\n- Prefer readable code over clever code. Add TODO comments, not partial systems.\n\n## Preferred Patterns\n- Use `find_symbol` / `read_file` to consult existing code before changes (never guess).\n- Use LSP tools (`lsp_definition`, `lsp_references`, `lsp_hover`, `lsp_diagnostics`) for\n  precise code intelligence \u2014 go-to-definition, find-all-references, type hovering, and\n  diagnostics. Prefer these over grep for understanding code structure.\n- Before non-trivial tasks, state your plan in 1-3 sentences.\n- Make parallel independent tool calls in one batch; only serialize when dependent.\n- Use `write_scratchpad` to track progress across turns.\n- Update STATE.txt after every completed change.\n- Every new feature needs at least one test.\n- If tests fail, stop and diagnose before making additional changes.\n\n\nREPOSITORY STATUS (git):\nCurrent branch: main\nM api.py\n M conftest.py\n M llm.py\n M mcp_server.py\n M tools/__init__.py\n M tools/mcp_client.py\n M tui_pt.py\n?? .mini_agent_memory_session_linux.db-shm\n?? .mini_agent_memory_session_linux.db-wal\n?? .mini_agent_memory_session_mpc_issue.db\n?? AUDIT_REPORT_mcp_conftest.md\n?? AUDIT_REPORT_subagent_architecture.md\n?? api_error.log\n?? logs/\n",
